lons2019 = df['lon'].tolist()

Make this Notebook Trusted to load map: File -> Trust Notebook
In[15]:
# create map with markers for room_type Entire home/apt and room type Private room
map2 = folium.Map(location=[46.2044, 6.1432], zoom_start=12)
for i in range(0, len(df)):
    if df.iloc[i]['room_type'] == 'Entire home/apt':
        folium.Marker([df.iloc[i]['lat'], df.iloc[i]['lon']], icon=folium.Icon(color='blue')).add_to(map2)
    else:
        folium.Marker([df.iloc[i]['lat'], df.iloc[i]['lon'],], icon=folium.Icon(color='green')).add_to(map2)

# add room_type and price as popup
for i in range(0, len(df)):
    folium.Marker([df.iloc[i]['lat'], df.iloc[i]['lon']],
                  popup=df.iloc[i]['room_type'] + ', Price: ' + str(df.iloc[i]['price']) + ' USD').add_to(map2)
map2

In[26]:
# calcutalte p-values for the correlation matrix
p_values = pd.DataFrame()
for x in corr.columns:
    for y in corr.columns:
        p_values.loc[x, y] = round(stats.pearsonr(df[x], df[y])[1], 4)
p_values

In[27]:
# create a correlation matrix with the p-values included as stars and their significance
p_values_significance = p_values.applymap(lambda x: '***' if x < 0.001 else ('**' if x < 0.01 else ('*' if x < 0.05 else ('.' if x < 0.1 else ''))))
corr_with_significance = corr.astype(str) + p_values_significance
corr_with_significance

# print the the definition of p-values
print('***: p-value < 0.001')
print('**: p-value < 0.01')
print('*: p-value < 0.05')
print('.: p-value < 0.1')

# round the correlation matrix to 4 decimal places and still include the p-values
corr_p = corr.round(3).astype(str) + p_values_significance
corr_p
